{{Infobox football league season |competition=[[A-Division (Bhutan)]] |season=2004 |winners=[[Transport United]] |relegated= |continentalcup1=[[2005 AFC President's Cup|AFC President's Cup]] |continentalcup1 qualifiers=[[Transport United]] |continentalcup2= |continentalcup2 qualifiers= |league topscorer= |biggest home win= |biggest away win= |highest scoring= |matches= |total goals= |longest wins= |title= |longest unbeaten= |longest losses= |prevseason=[[2003 A-Division|2003]] |nextseason=[[2005 A-Division|2005]] }}
The 2004 season of the [[A-Division (Bhutan)|Bhutanese A-Division]] was the tenth recorded season of top-flight football in [[Bhutan]]. The league was won by [[Transport United]], their first title.<ref name="RSSSF2004">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/bhutan04.html|title=Bhutan 2004|last=Schöggl|first=Hans|date=4 Jan 2006|website=www.rsssf.com|publisher=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=27 June 2014}}</ref> Transport United were Bhutan's representatives in the [[2005 AFC President's Cup]].<ref name="RSSSF2004" />
