'''Benson Veteran Cycle Museum''' is a [[private museum]] of [[History of the bicycle|veteran cycles]] in the village of [[Benson, Oxfordshire|Benson]] near [[Wallingford, Oxfordshire|Wallingford]] in [[Oxfordshire]], [[England]].<ref name="visitthames">{{cite web| url=https://www.visitthames.co.uk/things-to-do/benson-veteran-cycle-museum-p55223 | title=Benson Veteran Cycle Museum | website=www.visitthames.co.uk | publisher=River Thames | location=UK | accessdate=2 August 2017 }}</ref><ref name="information-britain">{{cite web| url=http://www.information-britain.co.uk/showPlace.cfm?Place_ID=11595 | title=Benson Veteran Cycle Museum | publisher=Information Britain | website=www.information-britain.co.uk | location=UK | accessdate=2 August 2017 }}</ref>
The museum has over 500 cycles dating from 1818 to 1930, with associated documentation and records.<ref name="westoxon">{{cite web| url=https://westoxon.org.uk/online-leaflet/benson-veteran-cycle-museum | title=Benson Veteran Cycle Museum | publisher=Oxfordshire Events | website=westoxon.org.uk | location=UK | accessdate=2 August 2017 }}</ref> The museum is open by appointment. There is a Benson Veteran Cycle Club annual rally on the first Sunday of July each year.
==See also== * [[History of the bicycle]] * [[History of cycling]] * [[List of museums in Oxfordshire]]
