{{Infobox sportsperson | name = Shashikala Kumarasinghe | nickname = | nationality = Sri Lankan | birth_date = 1983 | birth_place = | residence = | education = | country = {{SRI}} | sport = [[Archery]] | club = [[Colombo Archery Club]] }}
'''Harshani Shashikala Kumarasinghe''' (born 1984) is a Sri Lankan archer. She competed at the [[2010 Asian Games]] in the [[Archery at the 2010 Asian Games – Women's individual|archery event]].
Shashikala Kumarasinghe also returned to represent the national archery team in an international competition after 7 years by participating in the [[2016 South Asian Games]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pressreader.com/sri-lanka/daily-mirror-sri-lanka/20160129/282527247459318|title=Fifteen archers for SAG|work=Daily Mirror |publisher=Press Reader|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sundaytimes.lk/100110/Sports/spt17.html|title=Archers aim for SAF Gold|website=www.sundaytimes.lk|access-date=2017-10-23}}</ref>
